    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Protect Livery Drivers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Simon Arpiarian letter suggests New York City issue guns to livery drivers and train them in gun safety (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Another Livery Driver Is Slain, Pushing Toll to 9 for the Year'' (news article, April 29): Two weeks ago, Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani created a program to install bullet-proof barriers in livery vehicles. While this measure is well intentioned, it serves only to defend livery drivers from one angle of attack. A better plan would include deterrence measures.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Another Livery Driver Is Slain, Pushing Toll to 9 for the Year'' (news article, April 29): Two weeks ago, Mayor Rudolph W. Giuliani created a program to install bullet-proof barriers in livery vehicles. While this measure is well intentioned, it serves only to defend livery drivers from one angle of attack. A better plan would include deterrence measures.</p>
        <p>Instead of destroying guns from gun buy-back programs, the city should issue working models to livery drivers and train them in gun safety. Those planning an attack will have to reconsider the vulnerability of their intended prey, whether or not livery drivers actually accept these guns.</p>
        <p>SIMON ARPIARIAN  Atlanta, April 29, 2000</p>
      </block>
